</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-82_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To maximise the effectiveness of training programs, residential care homes should:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-85_ pf-text-1">Ensure all training is aligned with the latest regulatory requirements and best practices.




















































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-87_ pf-text-1">Foster a culture of continuous learning and development.




































































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-89_ pf-text-1">Utilise feedback from staff and residents to tailor training programs.



































































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-91_ pf-text-1">Engage with professional bodies and local health services to keep abreast of evolving care needs and standards.




































































